        "text": ", which means ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "father of a king",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and was the name of the royal family of Gerar, was given to Abimelech as a significant surname, and was perhaps one of the causes which induced him to seize the kingdom. A third phrase is found in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 23:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
