        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 9:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and to this son he gave the name of Abimelech, i.e., king's father. את־שׁמו ויּשׂם is not the same as את־שׁמו קרא, to give a person a name, but signifies to add a name, or give a surname (see ",
        "children": []
      },
